acceleration, and so on--

12
00:00:33 --> 00:00:39
then you can make the
conversions very easily.

13
00:00:35 --> 00:00:41
If you remember that the kinetic
energy is one-half m v squared,

14
00:00:39 --> 00:00:45
then the kinetic energy
of rotation then becomes

15
00:00:41 --> 00:00:47
one-half I omega squared.

